    <h2><a href="articles/if-you-send-a-newsletter-and-your-unsubscribe-link-requi---">If you send a newsletter and your unsubscribe link requi...</a></h2>
    <div class="variables">
    <div class="date">@date=2011-09-23</div>
    <div class="tags">@tags=<a href="tags/google-plus-post">google-plus-post</a></div>
    </div>
    <article>
        <p>It is simple:</p>
<p>If you send a newsletter and your unsubscribe link requires me to log in, fill out a form, or do anything for that matter, I go back to the email and just mark as spam.</p>
<p>If you are too lazy to make it easy to opt out, I am too lazy to help you with your email deliverability. </p>
<p>Unsubscribe links should be one click, easy to find, and not waste my time.</p>

    </article>
    
